New Records: Harry Kane scored his 26th and 27th goals in 35 appearances at Wembley for his country; already the most of any England player at the venue.
Lille’s Angel Gomes became the first player to start for England while playing for a French club since Marseille’s Trevor Steven in June 1992 (v France).
Key Match Events: Harry Kane scored twice on his landmark night wearing golden boots as he set about hunting down a new goalscoring target

Kane broke the deadlock with a blistering second half strike. He added a second after being fed the ball in the box by substitute Noni Madueke and capped off a night to remember with another superb win.
Pre-Game Insights: Harry Kane was sporting a pair of golden boots as England took on Finland in his 100th appearance for the national side – and scored twice wearing the new footwear.
Harry Kane was awarded a gold cap to mark his 100th England appearance on Tuesday night (10 September) - but the celebration was all too much for his young son.
Post-Match Reflections: Harry Kane spoke in the post-match press conference about his journey to 100 caps and his future with the national team.
Noni Madueke spoke to BBC Radio 5 Live about his debut and the support he received from his teammates.
Miscellaneous Highlights: England remained unbeaten against Finland, with this their 10th victory across their 12 meetings (drawn two). They've won their four home games against the Finns by an aggregate score of 11-2.
Lee Carsley is the first England manager to win his first two competitive games and keep a clean sheet in both since Steve McClaren in 2006.
